<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870921-0104 </DOCNO><HL> Treasury Will Offer$9.25 Billion of Bills</HL><DD> 09/21/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> FINANCIAL, INSURANCE, MUTUAL FUNDS, ACCOUNTING, LEASING (FIN)BOND MARKET NEWS (BON)TREASURY DEPARTMENT (TRE) </IN><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   The Treasury said it plans to pay down $575 million on the federal debt with the sale Sept. 29 of about $9.25 billion in 52-week bills. Maturing bills outstanding total $9.83 billion.    The bills will be dated Oct. 1 and will mature Sept. 29, 1988.    Tenders for the bills, available in minimum denominations of $10,000, must be received by 1 p.m. EDT Sept. 29 at the Treasury or at Federal Reserve banks or branches.    The Treasury said it would postpone the sale unless it is assured that Congress will raise the statutory debt ceiling before the scheduled auction date. </TEXT></DOC>